Cody slipped into the room, Lulu treading close behind. He looked around warily. It appeared every bit as empty, with the
exception of the stair and the armor, as it had earlier appeared to be. “Of course, appearances can be deceiving,” he said
to himself, giving the room a second once-over. “Especially appearances that have already appeared the same in appearance.”
He thought about that for a moment, then gave up and continued on.
